ax fæcyd, æmæ kæjdær ærdīag ærbajq˳yst</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>раздался выстрел и послышались чьи-то вопли</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a shot rang out and someone’s scream was heard</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1934 II 4</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ærdewagæ gængæ niccudæncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>с воплями они спустились</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they went down screaming</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>20%l2%l</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru"><bibl><author>Вс. Миллер</author></bibl> сопоставляет с <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>driwika-</w> <gloss><q>стоны</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘вопли’ ( <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_IF"/><biblScope>21, стр. 325</biblScope></bibl>). Сближение с <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ardawyn"/> ‘подстрекать’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>) не удовлетворительно ни с звуковой, ни со смысловой стороны.</etym><etym xml:lang="en"><bibl><author>Vs. Miller</author></bibl>compares the word of interest with <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>driwika-</w> <gloss><q>moans</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘wails’ ( <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_IF"/><biblScope>21, p. 325</biblScope></bibl>). The approach to <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ardawyn"/> ‘to incite’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>) is not satisfactory hypothesis on the sound part and on the meaning part.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>